  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales & Application Engineer",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Sales & Application Engineer</strong></h3><p><em>(Training Provided | Engineering Background Preferred)</em></p><p>If you are engineering-trained, self-motivated, and enjoy working with both people and technical solutions, we invite you to join our team as a <strong>Sales & Application Engineer</strong>.</p><p>This role is suitable for <strong>fresh graduates or early-career engineers</strong> who want exposure to <strong>engineering applications, customer interaction, and business development</strong>. On-the-job training will be provided.<br /></p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Maintain and strengthen relationships with existing customers</p></li><li><p>Develop new business opportunities for company products (e.g. pumps and spare parts)</p></li><li><p>Handle RFQs, prepare quotations, and follow up with customers</p></li><li><p>Attend to technical enquiries and propose suitable engineering solutions</p></li><li><p>Assist with tender documents, technical documentation, and manuals</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal teams to ensure timely and accurate support</p></li><li><p>Occasional travel within the region may be required<br /></p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>Certificate / Diploma in Engineering</strong></p></li><li><p>With or without relevant experience (training will be provided)</p></li><li><p>Basic engineering knowledge with willingness to learn</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated, responsible, and able to work independently</p></li><li><p>Good team player with a positive working attitude</p></li><li><p>Possession of <strong>Class 2 / 3 driving licence</strong> is an advantage<br /></p></li></ul><h3><strong>Why Join Us</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Structured on-the-job training and hands-on exposure</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to develop both <strong>technical and commercial skills</strong></p></li><li><p>Stable working environment with long-term career prospects</p></li><li><p><strong>Well-performing candidates may be selected for overseas training</strong></p></li></ul>",
